# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - All major entities (Resource, Application, TT, CR, Event, Agent, Location) are created.
# - Each entity has rdf:type, rdfs:label, rdfs:comment/skos:example.
# - Multiple properties are used for each entity type.
# - Relationships are established between different types of entities (e.g., Resource managed by Agent, TT related to Service/Resource/Agent/Event, CR impacting Resource/Application/Agent).
# - KOS concepts are used correctly.
# - No ldp prefix.
# - Logical blocks are maintained.
# - The graph is dense and connected, reflecting a complex IT environment.
